			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well as to a reason for having 2 pets (or more) really it goes back to the basis of the class I think. Magicians are supposed to be the master summoners/ pet class. I always felt magicians should do their damage through their pets not nukes. Imagine if the magician class had been set up so that at the lowest levels it is pretty much as it is now. As the magician gains in power they can summon more and more pets (all of which are commanded at once) but their nukes don't scale up anywhere nearly as much. Instead they get more spells which enhance the pets (or better summoned equipment). Yes a magician would need some set up time to summon his pets and properly buff/equip them. And a big problem would be going LD which would destroy the pets. But it would make the magician a very different class then the wizard. And while I love magicians many seem to feel they are little more then wizards with smaller nukes. Not true of course but the way the game has developed has left the magician more like wizards then they should be. Druids, shamans and clerics all share some abilities but are extremely different from each other. I would have liked to see this kind of difference at the higher end of the game between wizards and magicians. But I am afraid this isn't possible as that would be an entire revamp of the magician class.<br />_________________<br />Hilbur Helpmate
<br />
Archon of Brell
<br />
Unspoken Legacy</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
